<task id="002" project="ai-json-prompt-schema-system">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create PromptSchemaRenderer Service with Format Detection</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, api, implement</tags>
    <estimate>3h</estimate>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Create the PromptSchemaRenderer service that detects format (flat text vs JPS JSON) and renders JPS schemas into assembled prompt strings.</goal>
    <context>
      The renderer replaces the static BuildExecutionPrompt method in GenericAnalysisHandler.cs (L408-456).
      It's a pure function: given a raw prompt string, resolved scopes, template context, and downstream node info,
      it produces a deterministic RenderedPrompt (PromptText + optional JsonSchema).
      Format detection: null/empty → delegate to defaults, flat text → legacy path, JPS JSON (starts with { and contains $schema) → schema path.
      The rendering pipeline assembles sections in order: role → task → constraints → context → document → parameters → prior outputs → skills → knowledge → examples → output instructions.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Register as concrete type (no interface) per ADR-010
      - Pure function design: given inputs → deterministic output
      - Flat text path MUST produce output identical to current BuildExecutionPrompt
      - Use System.Text.Json for deserialization
      - MUST NOT log prompt content per ADR-015
      - Handle malformed JSON gracefully (fall back to flat text with warning)
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-json-prompt-schema-system/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-json-prompt-schema-system/spec.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/GenericAnalysisHandler.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/analysis-scopes.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/service-registration.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read GenericAnalysisHandler.BuildExecutionPrompt (L408-456) to understand current rendering logic</step>
    <step order="2">Read design.md "Composition Rendering Pipeline" and "Assembled Prompt Example" sections</step>
    <step order="3">Create `Services/Ai/PromptSchemaRenderer.cs` with:
      - Render() method signature matching design.md
      - Format detection logic (null/empty, flat text, JPS JSON)
      - Schema parsing via System.Text.Json
      - Section-by-section assembly (11 sections in order)
      - RenderedPrompt return type</step>
    <step order="4">Implement flat text legacy path that replicates BuildExecutionPrompt behavior exactly</step>
    <step order="5">Implement JPS rendering path with all section types</step>
    <step order="6">Verify build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Write</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
    <tool>Glob</tool>
    <tool>Grep</tool>
    <tool>Bash(dotnet build)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PromptSchemaRenderer.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Format detection correctly routes null/empty, flat text, and JPS JSON</criterion>
    <criterion>Flat text path produces identical output to current BuildExecutionPrompt</criterion>
    <criterion>JPS rendering assembles all 11 sections in correct order</criterion>
    <criterion>Malformed JSON falls back to flat text gracefully</criterion>
    <criterion>Project builds without errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
